<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-08-13T08:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-08-13T08:00:00-05:00" n="693" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d693">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">834.00 Revolutions/18: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Paraguay</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Howard</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Asunción</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-08-13T09:00:00-04:00">August 13, 1937—9
                                a.m.</date><lb/>[Received 1:25 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>15. During early morning hours some slight disturbances in the city.
                            Early morning delivery services suspended, streetcars not running,
                            intermittent telephone service, ex-service men being called in and many
                            other individuals in streets being impressed, cars coming into city
                            being searched. At this moment some 200 troops equipped with machine
                            guns are abiding near home of President Franco. Large number of troops
                            just passing Legation en route to center.</p>
                        <p>Copy to Buenos Aires.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Howard</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>